tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glucosuria, bilirubinuria, and abnormal urine appearance, suggesting impaired renal function, likely chronic kidney disease with possible nephrotic features. Elevated chloride and low COâ may indicate metabolic acidosis. Blood glucose and HbA1c are within normal limits, making diabetes less likely. Recommend urgent nephrology evaluation and further workup for renal pathology.
